<Class name="CM_VesselTerminalData" id="3137c2ac-5c09-4426-aaae-d954001542a2">
    <superclass name="CM_Object"/>
    <persistentAllowed/>
    <sharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassPersistentAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <access>protected</access>
    <text>This stores a Vessel's setting for each Terminal thet it will visit (myTerminal is the key).</text>
    <DbClassMap file="vessel"/>
    <PrimAttribute name="defaultDraftArrival" id="41766721-35c3-44fc-9ef6-9eeed490414c">
        <precision>12</precision>
        <scaleFactor>2</scaleFactor>
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Decimal"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="defaultDraftDeparture" id="11e1e6a2-3166-4254-ab8b-3429ca74cbc5">
        <precision>12</precision>
        <scaleFactor>2</scaleFactor>
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Decimal"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="grossDischargeTime" id="ad4b1965-c769-4e03-a26b-9b203d26c405">
        <precision>12</precision>
        <scaleFactor>2</scaleFactor>
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Decimal"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <text>The expected gross that the ship will be in a discharging port (from arrival at the port until ready to sail).
This will default to the value stored against the Terminal.  It is envisaged that the
valuies will be:

	o Weipa		1.3 days
	o CAR		3 days
	o QAL		2 days

These values can be changed by the users at any time.</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="grossLoadingTime" id="cfed0549-9c18-4d56-876f-8f99c1fab083">
        <precision>12</precision>
        <scaleFactor>2</scaleFactor>
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Decimal"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <text>The expected gross that the ship will be in a loading port (from arrival at the port until ready to sail).
This will default to the value stored against the Terminal.  It is envisaged that the
valuies will be:

	o Weipa		1.3 days
	o CAR		3 days
	o QAL		2 days

These values can be changed by the users at any time.</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="isUseTerminalDefaults" id="7e292c5f-b16d-4abd-9804-de57b3302f7b">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Boolean"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <ImplicitInverseRef name="myPreferredBerth" id="1e27ea3d-4862-4009-8677-8f07b9da91dc">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="HMS_Berth"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
    </ImplicitInverseRef>
    <ExplicitInverseRef name="myTerminal" id="8d0f2f13-448d-41d2-aec5-a029b2c0f809">
        <kind>child</kind>
        <transientToPersistentAllowed/>
        <updateMode>manual</updateMode>
        <embedded/>
        <type name="CM_Terminal"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <Inverse name="CM_Terminal::allVesselTerminals"/>
    </ExplicitInverseRef>
    <ExplicitInverseRef name="myVessel" id="5500b6ca-69cb-471b-934c-265a27e4458e">
        <kind>child</kind>
        <transientToPersistentAllowed/>
        <updateMode>manual</updateMode>
        <embedded/>
        <type name="CM_Vessel"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <Inverse name="CM_Vessel::allTerminalDatas"/>
    </ExplicitInverseRef>
    <PrimAttribute name="nextNumber" id="9a3cc1b9-cc86-4ce5-a7f8-5a2f3f4aef4a">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Integer"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="nonChargeTime" id="e1fc6d47-9951-4be5-ada0-d6ceac5dbe96">
        <precision>12</precision>
        <scaleFactor>2</scaleFactor>
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Decimal"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <text>The number of hours after the arrival time at the harbour before charing begins.
Form non-dedicated ships, this is typically 12 hours.  For dedicated ships, this
can be set to zero.</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="stopChargingAt" id="6cfdb3f0-fe29-4efa-b586-5cc69f9d26b4">
        <length>31</length>
        <embedded/>
        <type name="String"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <text>Refer to "STOP_CHARGING_" class constants on CM_Terminal.  Currently
two options are available to stop charging when:

	o Complete Loading/Discharge
	o Sail</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="vesselDischargeRate" id="662982f8-4c67-4ac5-8718-6a3abcf32aa9">
        <precision>12</precision>
        <scaleFactor>2</scaleFactor>
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Decimal"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <text>The standard discharge rate for the vessel in tonnes per hour.</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="vesselDownTime" id="b7181978-f0e9-4319-8b07-b55ad99c0962">
        <precision>12</precision>
        <scaleFactor>2</scaleFactor>
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Decimal"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <text>The number of hours at the wharf where the vessel is neither loading nor discharging cargo.
This will default to the value stored against the Terminal (see CMIF_ConfigTerminal).

Note, this does not include time spent alongside waiting for the tide.</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="vesselLoadRate" id="05593981-c045-4d75-9b6d-11daacd27c97">
        <precision>12</precision>
        <scaleFactor>2</scaleFactor>
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Decimal"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <text>The standard load rate for the vessel in tonnes per hour.

Gross load time = cargo quantity / net rate + operational down time</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <JadeMethod name="cloneMe" id="30af5504-1dc7-4e9f-9f44-b4dcafcee42a">
        <source>cloneMe(_isTransient:Boolean):SelfType;
// --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Created:		28 August 2006 by cnwdad1
//
// Purpose:		Returns a clone of the receiver.
//
// Parameters:	_isTransient - True if the clone should be a transient object.
//
// Returns:		A reference to the clone object.
//
// Changed On	Changed By	Reason
// ----------	----------	-------------------------------------------------------
//
// --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
vars
	cloneObj	: SelfType;
	
begin
	cloneObj					:=	self.cloneSelf(_isTransient);
	cloneObj.myPreferredBerth	:= 	self.myPreferredBerth;
	cloneObj.myTerminal			:=	self.myTerminal;
	
	return cloneObj;
end;</source>
        <Parameter name="_isTransient" type="Boolean"/>
        <ReturnType type="SelfType"/>
    </JadeMethod>
    <JadeMethod name="defaultDraftArrival" id="5b4f3f24-6e60-4946-bb16-7628d7e71ae0">
        <methodInvocation>mapping</methodInvocation>
        <source>defaultDraftArrival(set : Boolean; _value : Decimal io) mapping;
// --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Created:		07 June 2007 by cnwdad1
//
// Changed On	Changed By	Reason
// ----------	----------	-------------------------------------------------------
//
// --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
begin
	if self.isUseTerminalDefaults and (not set) then
		_value	:=	self.myTerminal.getConfig(VesselDraftArrival).Decimal;
	endif;
end;</source>
        <Parameter name="set" type="Boolean"/>
        <Parameter name="_value" type="Decimal" usage="io"/>
    </JadeMethod>
    <JadeMethod name="defaultDraftDeparture" id="43393459-4680-4d5a-b068-eac8c2d63be1">
